access: The apartment is yours! You have full access to everything with exception to the secret door that leads to our underground lair (just kidding! about the lair part).
additional_house_rules:
We hope that you enjoy your stay, and we will be ready to take any questions by phone or text during your visit.

Keys, typically are always handed to you at Check-in and we will be waiting at the apartment for your arrival. 

Standard check-in is any time between 2pm and 5pm. earlier check-in can be arranged for $35, paid through Airbnb.

Check-out time is at 11am.

Late check-out after 11am (before 3pm) will be billed at $50 cash. If the room is empty by 11am, and you need us to hold luggage until later in the day, the bag storage fee is $25.

If you wish to have an early check-in, or a late check-out, please let us know when you book - we are flexible as occupancy or circumstance dictate.

For the safety and security of our guests and neighbors, no additional visitors or guests of any kind are allowed to enter the apartment during your stay; except to assist with check-in or check-out.

Late night cooking (after 10pm) is not allowed, with the exception of using the toaster and microwave.

Smoking is absolutely not allowed in our apartment or building.

Please enter and leave the apartment quietly as not to disturb the neighbors above and below you, and ALWAYS lock the door behind you as you come and go ensuring you have your keys on your person to avoid mutually inconvenient lockouts.

 If you plan on waking up and leaving the building early in the morning, please be mindful of sleeping neighbors. 

Please clean up after yourself in the kitchen and common areas. Sponges, scouring pads, towels and soap are all provided and always replenished for you to use in the kitchen.

Kindly refrain from eating in bed to avoid spillage and stains on the white linens.
description:
This fully-furnished apartment is close to Wineries, Local Shops, Upscale Restaurants, and a trove of other bespoke amenities.  You’ll stay in a historic brownstone convenient and centrally located: Within walking distance to Columbia University, St. John the Divine, Central Park North and other namesake areas throughout Harlem. Our place is good for Couples, Solo Adventurers, Culture Junkies, Travel Addicts, The Occasional Staycationers, and Wanderlusters alike.

Unique to the space, you enjoy exclusive access as our guest - no sharing with us. be greeted with hardwood floors, sun-cast floor-to-ceiling windows and the charm of exposed brick accent walls throughout. An truly spacious New York apartment featuring one-bedroom with two double beds, a living room that optionally sleeps one additional person, full service kitchen, full jacuzzi bath/shower, and open dining space.  
Although we won't wow you with an uber-modern bundle of amenities and minted renovations, you will, however, enjoy a well-appointed, floor-thru, brownstone style home while away from your home (wherever that may be in the world) offering you close access to Central Park and Restaurant Row.

•Fully Furnished, Including Two Double Beds
•Full Bath and Shower
•Full Galley-Style Kitchen
•Large Living room
•Communal Dining Space for shared meals
•Complimentary WIFI Internet Connectivity, Netflix, and Spotify Streaming Music
•Steps away from Central Park and public transportation
•Extra Linens and Towels Provided

The apartment is yours! You have full access to everything with exception to the secret door that leads to our underground lair (just kidding! about the lair part).

We hope that you enjoy your stay, and we will be ready to take any questions by phone or text to ensure your comfort during your visit.
We can periodically check in with you to make sure you are getting along well during your stay in NYC.

Our home is located in the Morningside Heights neighborhood steps to Harlem's posh "Gold Coast". We are centrally located to Columbia University. 
The neighborhood is very safe, well-populated, highly residential, family-oriented and is routinely patrolled by local NYPD. 

Various transportation options are nearby. The central-most metro (2 mins away) takes you to Times Square in just minutes - very convenient access-point to all areas of NYC.

Just blocks away from Central Park and The famed Apollo Theater.  The area is home to some of New York's most celebrated bars, cocktail lounges and eateries, while also anchoring a host of distinct cultural destinations. 

All located within walking distance of the flat  ...

We are located near the A, B, C, subway lines, and several different buses. We're about a 10-12 minute subway ride from Columbus Circle, and about 15-20 minutes to Times Square and Chelsea.

We are a very easy trip from LaGuardia Airport, as the M60 bus is just 12 blocks north of us from 125th Street. For JFK, simply take the A train to or from 125th Street directly to the airport!

If a car is more your style, cabs are usually available 1 block away, and Uber is a great option that can pick you up right at the apartment.

This home is on people’s minds. It’s been viewed 1506 times in the past week. We recommend you book right away to secure your stay.
